        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Problem getting the router, menu view helper and breadcrumbs view helper to work in sync.\r\n\r\nSample dump of {{$reqParams}} and {{$myParams}} at line 120 of {{Zend\\Navigation\\Page::isActive()}}, just before {{if (null !== $this->getRoute()}} on line 121:\r\n\r\n{code:title=$reqParams}\r\n  '__NAMESPACE__' => string 'Web\\Controller' (length=14)\r\n  'controller' => string 'Web\\Controller\\Tools' (length=20)\r\n  'action' => string 'calendar' (length=8)\r\n  '__CONTROLLER__' => string 'tools' (length=5)\r\n{code}\r\n{code:title=$myParams}\r\n  'controller' => string 'tools' (length=5)\r\n  'action' => string 'calendar' (length=8)\r\n{code}\r\nThe 'controller' key is checked to see if the page is active, which in this case fails, unless {{__CONTROLLER__}} is used for comparison.\r\n\r\n{code:title=portion of navigation config. Namespace is Web\\Controller}\r\n'Home' => array(\r\n    'label' => 'Home',\r\n    'route' => 'web',\r\n    'controller' => 'index',\r\n    'action' => 'index',\r\n),\r\n'Calendar' => array(\r\n    'label'  => 'Calendar',\r\n    'route' => 'web',\r\n    'controller' => 'tools',\r\n    'action' => 'calendar',\r\n),\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nIf 'controller' for 'Calendar' is set to 'Web\\Controller\\Tools', isActive would work but the href generated would be \/web\/Web\/Controller\/Tools\/calendar and not\/web\/tools\/calendar.\r\nThe breadcrumbs view helper detects 'Home' as the active page even though 'Calendar' is the actual active page.\r\n\r\n{code:title=router portion of module.config.php}\r\n'router' => array(\r\n    'routes' => array(\r\n        'web' => array(\r\n            'type'    => 'Zend\\Mvc\\Router\\Http\\Segment',\r\n            'options' => array(\r\n                'route'    => '\/web[\/:controller][\/:action]',\r\n                'constraints' => array(\r\n                    'controller' => '[a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9_-]*',\r\n                    'action'     => '[a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9_-]*',\r\n                ),\r\n                'defaults' => array(\r\n                    '__NAMESPACE__' => 'Web\\Controller',\r\n                    'controller'    => 'index',\r\n                    'action'        => 'index',\r\n                ),\r\n            ),\r\n            'may_terminate' => true,\r\n            'child_routes' => array(\r\n                'wildcard' => array(\r\n                    'type' => 'Zend\\Mvc\\Router\\Http\\Wildcard',\r\n                    'options' => array(\r\n                        'key_value_delimiter' => '\/',\r\n                        'param_delimiter' => '\/',\r\n                    ),\r\n                    'may_terminate' => true,\r\n                ),\r\n                'trailingSlash' => array(\r\n                    'type' => 'Zend\\Mvc\\Router\\Http\\Literal',\r\n                    'options' => array(\r\n                        'route'    => '\/',\r\n                        'defaults' => array(\r\n                        ),\r\n                    ),\r\n                ),\r\n            ),\r\n        ), \/\/ end web route\r\n    ), \/\/ end routes\r\n), \/\/ end router\r\n{code}\r\nThe other alternative might be to create a route for each page. But if there are 10 controllers each having 5 actions, 50 routes would need to be defined?"
        },
